<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Concerto: Open Source Digital Signage</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", media: "all", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "application", "data-turbolinks-track" => true %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>

<div class="main-nav">

  <div class="content">

    <div class="pure-menu pure-menu-open pure-menu-horizontal">
      <%= link_to page_path("overview"), class: "pure-menu-heading" do %><%= image_tag("ConcertoLogo_main-nav.png", :alt => "Concerto", :width => 200) %><% end %>

      <ul>
        <li class="<%= 'active' if current_page?(controller: 'pages', action: 'show', id: 'demo') %>"><%= link_to :controller => :pages, :action => :show, :id => "demo" do %><b>Try</b> Concerto<% end %></li><li class="<%= 'active' if current_page?(controller: 'pages', action: 'show', id: 'deploy') %>"><%= link_to :controller => :pages, :action => :show, :id => "deploy" do %><b>Deploy</b> Concerto<% end %></li><li class="<%= 'active' if current_page?(controller: 'pages', action: 'list_help') %>"><%= link_to :controller => :pages, :action => :list_help do %>Get <b>Help</b><% end %></li><li class="<%= 'active' if current_page?(controller: 'pages', action: 'list_blog') %>"><%= link_to :controller => :pages, :action => :list_blog do %><b>Blog</b><% end %></li><li id="nav-search-toggle"><a href="#"><i class="fa fa-search"></i></a></li><!-- search: hidden by default --><li id="nav-search"><input type="search"></input></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <%#= link_to "v1", :controller => :pages, :action => :show, :id => "v1" %>
    <%#= link_to "v1 Help", :controller => :pages, :action => :list_v1help %>

  </div>

</div>


<div class="stripe blue-images">
  <h1 class="center">Digital Signage for Everyone.</h1>
</div>


<div class="stripe">
  <div class="content expose">
    <div class="center expose-headline">
      <h1>What is Concerto?</h1>
      <h5>An open source digital signage package, Concerto allows you to share videos, graphic flyers, 
and text-based advertisements and target them to specific audiences.</h5>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="stripe">
  <div class="content expose">
    <div class="center expose-headline">
      <h1>Take a Look</h1>
      <h5>Concerto is designed from the ground up to be simple, quick, and elegant.</h5>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="stripe">
  <div class="content expose">
    <div class="center expose-headline">
      <h1>How to Get Started</h1>
      <h5>Concerto is comprised of two parts: a server and a content player.</h5>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="stripe">
  <div class="content expose">
    <div class="center expose-headline">
      <h1>What if I Need Help?</h1>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="content">
  <%= yield %>

  <br />



  <br />

  <h1>Header One</h1>
  <h2>Header Two</h2>
  <h3>Header Three</h3>
  <h4>Header Four</h4>
  <h5>Header Five</h5>
  <h6>Header Six</h6>

  <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Suspendisse et vulputate purus, vitae tincidunt ante. Maecenas tincidunt, magna at varius varius, enim justo imperdiet eros, et lacinia orci diam sit amet dolor. Cras aliquam dui mauris, et fermentum dui fringilla nec.</p>

  <a href="#" title="">Link tag illustration</a>
</div>



<div class="stripe blue-images center">
  <div class="content" style="padding: 1.8em 0 1.6em 0;">
    <%= image_tag("footer_logo.png", :alt => "Concerto") %>
  </div>
</div>

<div id="footer" class="stripe">
  <p>Footer content</p>
</div>


<div id="user_nav">
  <% if user_signed_in? %>
    Signed in as <%= current_user.name %>. Not you?
    <%= link_to "Sign out", destroy_user_session_path %>
  <% else %> 
    <%= link_to "Sign in", user_omniauth_authorize_path(:google_oauth2) %>
  <% end %>
</div>

</body>
</html>
